8. ‘But can Christ be in the same heart where sin is?’ Undoubtedly he can;
                    otherwise it never could be saved therefrom. Where the sickness is, there is the
                    physician,

And they are likewise holy and undefiled while they ‘walk after the Spirit’;
Rom. 8:1. although sensible there is another principle in them, and that ‘these are contrary to each other’.
Gal. 5:17.
